Description.Geographical Features:
A portion of Kryptgarden south of [[Phandalin]] was known as the '''Crooked Forest''' because some of the trees there had been bent by ancient creatures that dwelled there to indicate paths through the forest. Following the passage of [[Volothamp Geddarm]] through the area, the forest received more visitors than it had in decades, disturbing a number of [[treant]]s and [[blight]]s.{{Cite adventurers league/In Volo's Wake|?}}

[[File:Honor Among Thieves - Kryptgarden Forest orifice.jpg|thumb|right|250px|''The Underdark orifice. Rejected names: hole, pit, mouth, sinkhole, and shaft.'']]
A deep hole in the ground—known to some as "the orifice"—in the red forest east of the Sword Mountains led to the [[Underdark]] and a passage to the [[Hanging City of Dolblunde]].

document_data.History:
During the era of the [[First Flowering]], the forest that later came to be known as Kryptgarden was a part of the ancient [[elven]] realm of [[Illefarn]], which was founded ''circa'' {{Yearlink|-22900}}. The surface-dwelling dwarves of the briefling flourishing realm of [[Besilmer]], from {{Yearlink|-4420}} to {{Yearlink|-4160}}, also had borders reaching Kryptgarden Forest.

The [[green dragon]] [[Claugiyliamatar]] established her lair within the Kryptgarden Forest in the {{YearlinkName|1303}}.

In the {{YearlinkName|1489}}, the [[Five Factions]] all gathered in the forest to deal with the rising threat of the renewed [[Cult of the Dragon]].{{Cite adventurers league/Corruption in Kryptgarden|7}} The cult's ''[[Green Dragon Mask]]'' was recovered from the lair of Claugiyliamatar in Kryptgarden Forest. Old Gnawbone herself was injured while blows were struck against the [[Red Wizards of Thay]], the Cult of the Dragon, and the [[Zartruss]] [[hobgoblin]] clan.{{cite web/Critical Spoilers: Season One}}

Around the {{YearlinkName|1491}}, the undead servants of [[Ularun Mortus]] passed through Kryptgarden in an ongoing assault against the lair of Claugiyliamatar.{{Cite web/D&D Beyond/Sleeping Dragon's Wake|15}}

In the late 1490s DR,{{HAT-time}} [[Xenk Yendar]] led a party comprising [[Edgin Darvis]], [[Holga Kilgore]], [[Simon Aumar]], and [[Doric]] into the Kryptgarden Forest to find the orifice into the Underdark.{{Cite video/Honor Among Thieves}}

document_data.Notable Locations:
* [[Cult stronghold]], a temporary, fortified settlement established by the Cult of the Dragon.{{Cite adventurers league/Corruption in Kryptgarden|13}}
* [[Deeping Cave]], lair of the green dragon Claugiyliamatar. It lay in a deep ravine at the base of one of the bordering mountains.{{Cite dragon/233/Wyrms of the North: Claugiyliamatar|33-37}}
* [[Southkrypt Garden]], an abandoned silver mine that once housed a community of [[dwarves]].
* A ''[[portal]]'' in a cave led to [[Vanrakdoom]], a [[Sharran]] temple in [[Undermountain]].<ref>{{Cite web enhancement/Vanrakdoom|11}}
* [[Uncle's Keep]], a dwarf-built keep that was part of deeds granted by the [[Lords of Waterdeep]] and received in an inheritance.{{Cite dungeon/26/The Inheritance|6-9}}

Inhabitants.Notable Inhabitants:
* [[Claugiyliamatar]], the monstrous green dragon also known as "Old Gnawbone" who terrorized anything and everything that passed through her domain.
* King [[Witchthorn]], a [[verdant prince]] and ruler of the [[fey]] in Kryptgarden Forest.{{Cite adventurers league/Corruption in Kryptgarden|25-26}}
* [[Ishaldra]], a [[dryad]] who studied evil magic.
